description: Allegro 5 is a cross-platform library mainly aimed at video game and multimedia programming. It handles common, low-level tasks such as creating windows, accepting user input, loading data, drawing images, playing sounds, etc. and generally abstracting away the underlying platform. However, Allegro is not a game engine: you are free to design and structure your program as you like.
releaseNotes: Please refer to the online release notes at http://liballeg.org/changes-5.2.html
title: Allegro Game Programming Library
